Headless mode allows the wiki engine to run in an API-only mode. This allows custom frontends to be implemented on top of the wiki engine. Enabling headless mode essentially disables the web frontend.

## How it works

By prefixing the URL pathname with `/api`, you can access the raw JSON data that is used to generate the page. For example,

- `/wiki/HeadlessMode` &rarr; returns an HTML page
  - `/api/wiki/HeadlessMode` &rarr; returns the data used to generate the above page
- `/wiki/HeadlessMode?action=edit` &rarr; returns an HTML edit form
  - `/api/wiki/HeadlessMode?action=edit` &rarr; returns JSON data used to generate the form